# Packet Mutator

## Description

Within this repository, a library is available which encompasses the necessary functionality to effectuate mutations of received packets from packetdrill. The library accommodates the following protocols:


- User Datagram Protocol (UDP)
- Transmission Control Protocol (TCP)
- Internet Protocol version 4 (IPv4)
- Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6)


The mutations that can be performed via this library are as follows:

- Replacement: Modifying the value of a specific protocol's field.
- Insertion: Adding a sequence of bytes at a designated position within the packet.
- Truncation: Removing the final segment of a packet based on a given offset.


## Build

To build this library you have to run the following command:

```
make
```

This command create the object files that are needed for packetdrill